
Write a program that returns the sum of all multiples of 3 or 5 below the given number.
Additionally, if the number is negative, return 0.
Note: If a number is a multiple of both 3 and 5, count it only once.

Example: If we list all the natural numbers below 10 that are multiples of 3 or 5, we get 3, 5, 6, and 9. The sum of these multiples is 

public class MultiplesOf3And5 {

    public static int sumOfMultiples(int number) {
        if (number < 0) {
            return 0; // Negatif sayı için 0 döndür
        }
        
        int sum = 0;
        
        // 3 veya 5'in katlarını bul ve topla
        for (int i = 0; i < number; i++) {
            if (i % 3 == 0 || i % 5 == 0) {
                sum += i;
            }
        }
        
        return sum;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int input = 10; // Örnek giriş
        int result = sumOfMultiples(input);
        
        System.out.println("Sonuç: " + result); // Çıktı: 23
    }
}
